<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Okay I did some predictions on Everquest forums before that game came out and 90% came out the way I predicted so I'll try my luck at SB :P heh and these r just opinions btw. I still love the idea of SB and will be one of the first to buy and play it. I'll only do 5 cuz im tired and wanna go to sleepy.<P>1. This games gonna produce a hella lot of naked pkr's EQ didn't think it would be a problem but last I checked all the PvP servers in EQ were coin loot only. I know u get 3 bonded items but the rest of ur junk is up for grabs and since money is gonna play a big role in SB there's gonna be 1000's of them. I say naked because the pk'r is not goin to fill his 3 bonded slots with his stuff untill he kills someone, so that will rule out the posibility of catching up to the pk'r and killing him for ur stuff back. And if u try saying that when someones get's pk'd they gonna spread the word and that person won't get out of the zone alive or wouldn't be able to hunt in that place any longer but pkr's even naked sissy ones always know a way out. There's gonna be some spell or some way of avoiding this.<P>2. Fact is all you people talk about how skill is gonna play a role in pking and how lvl's don't matter if u got skill hahaha yeah right. Let's face it 99.9999% of the time u get pk'd it's gonna be when ur almost dead with supa low health and barely able to walk when all the pk'r has to do is reach out his little finger and tap u to kill u, or when ur in the middle of fighting a creature. Not everyone is gonna want to hunt in groups and split loot or items and these people will be the targets.<P>3. Your never gonna have trouble finding a group. Fighting in a group will be the only way of avoiding prediction 1-2. With all the pkr's that r gonna be running around. If ur not a social person u better become one pretty quick  <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0">.<P>4. Well this is the prediction I hate the most but everyone's gonna be running around naked in fear. On the EQ PvP servers EVERYONE bagged EVERYTHING. I know Wp said that items wouldn't be that important or if u lost all ur items it wouldn't be the end of ur character and if u think that's gonna keep people from running around naked ur crazy. In EQ if u got pk'd the person got to loot one item only, did that stop people from goin naked!!! Hell No. It doesn't matter how small the item was cuz be honest after u worked hard and got the gold to buy that cloth sandal or pretty silk gloves last thing u wanted to do was lose it to some cheap naked pk'r that takes no risk to himself at all. Sorry for the references to EQ but it best suits my opinions.<P>5. Well another hard fact is that most people that will buy the game and PAY to play it will be the people walking into Walmart or whatever and seeing the game on the shelves. They're not gonna do any research on the game or put any thought into it. They're not gonna be the devoted RPG im sure all of us are lol. After a couple days or weeks of playing this game ur gonna see the forum's filling up with their post on unfairness and their whining about getting pk'd and losing their stuff or how someone killed them unfairly and cheaply with about a zillion other whining problems they got, and because they're paying and they outnumber us Wp's gonna have to listen to them!!! So prediction #5 is after 3-6 months u can bet there's gonna be some PvP changes towards item looting, exp loss, and anythign else these people will complain about.<P>And FYI I ran and was apart of some pk guilds in UO EQ Diablo AC. The guilds I was apart of did not cheat the game or the player. I was never naked or pk'd someone while fighting or low on health, we met on even terms and fought it out for the victory.
