Okay guys you need to go easy on the "WP protect me from suchandsuch."  I know many of you are jaded ex EQers, I am and I had my worries at first.  Then I started thinking about how much more fun this game is going to be if WP takes a back seat and lets us run the game, like they have said their goal is.  This is a player driven world and I dont think tolerating a few naked PK's is too high a price to pay for that.<P>Now on to why there will only be a few naked PK's and why the situations you bring up really aren't that practical.  Hopefully this will put your mind at ease a bit.<P>I'll reply point by point<P>1)First of all there is no "gate" or "recal" or anything that will let you escape your enemies territory quickly.  If you want to get somehwere you have to walk or run.  So even naked sissy PK's as you put it will have to find a way to get out of your guild lands with your loot.  On top of this everyone operates with their guild town as their base of operations.  There is no "bind" spell, the only way you can reset your bind point is if you bind yourself to <B>the</B> tree your guild or parent guild owns or a safehold tree.  So the only way for a naked PK to get out of there quickly with your loot is to bind it and get killed.  <B>BUT</B> and that is a big but mind you!!  I do not think you will be able to bind your items on the field.  I think that would be terribly stupid of WP and encourage exactly what you mention.  I am almost positive that you will need to return to your city and pay some kind of fee to soulbind items.  So the scenario now goes as follows.  Group of naked PKers enter your guild territory, they kill one of your members (say Bob) and take a couple of his items.  He respawns in town and says over the kindom channel "There are raiders in the south woods, I need help retrieving some gear and kicking them out!"  He gets 9 of his buddies together and maybe they take a few NPC guards and go romp on the naked PKers.  A few of Bob's friend die but they kill all of the PKers, they retrieve Bob's items (because you cant bind in the field).  Now the naked PKers respawn a 15 minute walk away with nothing to show for their time but some -exp and a good fight.<P>2) I have never said level wont matter.  Level will matter a great deal, it is just that at higher levels these differences wont matter as much.  Right now a level 20 will whup the crap out of a level 10 but a level 70 has a chance against a level 80 if he has skills that counter the 80's skills and uses them wisely.  I also dont think your example of getting ganked while you are low on health after fighting a monster is a good example either.  You will mostly be fighting monsters early in your SB career, after you have a main character that is up in the 70's hopefully you will move on to GvG activities or the boys over at WP are going to feel like they haven't dont their job well.  Now when you are still leveling, idealy you will be in a full group of guildmates (more exp and fun for everyone, why not?) you will be in your guilds territory so the only real PKing you have to worry about is your punk friend who thinks it would be funny if you had to walk back to your corpse only to find your pants missing =P.  Sure there will be people who want to solo and who want to explore outside of guild lands alone, but they take the risk that they have no one to watch their backs and may get killed by some lowbie while they are healing up and out of combat mode, it is just a risk you have to accept.<P>2.5) I am going to insert a little something here that I think you should consider.  You seem to be seperating the PK's from everyone else.  I know I did at first when I came over from EQ.  The PK's on RZ were the few who did hunt other players and were considered outcasts.  I hope the vast majority of SB players are what we considered PK's.  They engage in PvP combat on a regular basis.  I dont know about you but once I get to the mid levels in SB I am going to try and level to the soft cap by hunting other players.  By that time I figure I will be tired of hunting mobs and looking to learn the ways of PvP and to fight some challenging battles against human opponents.<P>3) I'm glad we see eye to eye here.  I dont think SB will have many of the problems that EQ had with groups, the level restrictions, the unfair exp split, etc.  Grouping is good for everyone involved no matter what.  Everyone gets more exp in the end and it will make hunting/raiding/exploring easier.<P>4) Your prediction about everyone running around naked and in fear reflects poorly on you buddy   <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"> . Again I will refer you to my adamant belief that items are not bindable on the field.  I will try to get some kind of official word on that.  I just cant see this happening, not with the type of gamer I think SB will draw.  I think it is going to pull in a lot of the CS/Q3/UT/T2 crowd that doesn't play EQ because fighting bots is boring.  r0xx0ring bots in games like Half-Life and Tribes doesn't mean shait, real people will own you if you think you are good because you can own bots.<P>5) Again I dont think the type of people you mention will play SB for more than the free trial period.  Anyone that whines about anything is going to be an immediate target for drastic, righteous retribution.  MANY of the SB fans are ex-EQers that are sick and tired of the vocal minority spoiling it for everyone.  I would pray to a god if I belived in them that you will have to post under your highest level characters name on the forums once the game goes gold.  That would nip all that whining crap in the bud real fast.<P>As far as your suggestions about limiting the naked PKer syndrome, I think the best/easiest solution is to not make items bindable on the field.  That way they still have to make it out of your territory with your loot to keep it.  If they catch you out in the open, well that is mostly your fault and you better suck it up.<P>------------