I agree and disagree with you here certa.<P>Where I agree,<P>Binding an item in the field, you are probably correct. You wont be able to do this.  This would be a good way for people to get their stuff back.<P>from that point on i disagree...<P>There will ALWAYS be people looking for the easy out. There will be entire guilds devoted to it. One thing your forgetting is tactics. Bring 10 to 20 of your friends. Fully armored and ready to fight. Send in the naked fighters. Just scrape the territory of your enemy guild. Kill and take what you can. Bring the loot back to the 20 friends who are FULLY able to defend themselves. The angry hoard you say? One tactic that I love to use when PKing. RUN!! Run back to your guild land if you have to.. either way, you get the loot. Also dint i hear that you can fly? Out of combat mode of course. More tactics.. Kill a player, loot him or her, hand the loot to a friend who can fly. He deposits the loot you just got back at your guild. <P>Rinse and repeat. Its endless....<P>That is just one very simple tactic. You can be sure as the game goes on, many many more will follow. People will find a hole and exploit it. This will lead to total adjustments across the board.<P>BETA you say? You think there gonna squash this in BETA? Never happen. The few testers will be able to crack some bugs, yes. But nothing compared to what 300,000 people will find.<P>On a lighter note..<P>These problems wont really exist for us. We are waiting here for the game to release. Soon as it does, you know ill be logged in on the first day! We will advance, and so will many more. Tactics will be developed, powerful guilds will be formed.<P>Where it gets ugly again...<P>Where the problem comes in is when the newbie buys the game off the shelf 8 months later. Then you have extremely powerful guilds just harvesting newbies. People will get pissed " HELL I PAY FOR THIS GAME!!" and either quit, or complain and then quit. Revenue will drop, rumors will spread and people will not want to start playing this game just to be food for the strong.<P><BR>Your guild will defend them? Are you gonna sit around and watch some newbie hack away at mobs in your guild area? Just in case? maybe you would... maybe not. Would you do it all the time? No way. Even if you did, the attacks would stop. Until you got sick of sitting around doing nothing, then it would all begin again.<P>It will get to the point where something has to change. <P>So there you have it. A very negative outlook on the future of SB. Can it happen? Sure. Will it? We shall see. But if every angle is not looked into, there could be major problems.<P>So I wouldn’t downplay anything anyone says.  Don’t under estimate the power and tactics of PKers.
