I played on VZ as well.  I quit before item loot got screwed though.  I can almost understand why item loot was canceled though.  Melee needed it ALL.  Casters didn't need any.  Their game was not balanced for pvp and it showed.  Removing that aspect of the game was just admitting that.<P>EQ has tainted your mind.  Your concerns are unfounded because of that.  You are biased because of the system eq used and are basing your predictions upon eq.  I think all ex-eq players have gone through this, its understandable.  However, THIS IS <B>NOT</B> EQ.<P>I'm not going to further argue your points.  They have been argued in the past.  I would like to say something though.  You are thinking far too short term.  Yes a pker may come into your land (not necessarily an easy task in itself) steal your item and run away.  But you have his name.  You have his guild name.  You can find out where to strike back.  Getting even isn't something that has to be done instantaneously.  <P>Besides how many times do you think this is going to work?  You think bob is going to buy his stuff back and run back to his spot and solo and get killed on a daily basis?  No he will adapt.<P>Pro EQ - What you consider a problem I consider an act of war, a part of the game.  This game was created for a niche market.  I'm sure some people will quit because of that.  But others will give the game a try and fall in love with it for the same reasons.  <P>Anyway Grendal if any of your points are right sure I'll say, "wtg man, good call."  But instead I think your going to be saying, "Wow they put more thought into this than I ever realized.  This game is cool!"<P>P.S. Items don't matter.  Don't worry about them.<P>P.S.S. Certa: pretty sure Ashen recently said that once your bound to a guild owned city you can't rebind to a gm town as long as you own a city.
