<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Sargeras, an act of war? Yes. These actions would be considered an act of war. That’s if you can keep in a roleplaying perspective. The problem is, these people are item hunters, power gamers, money mongers.. you get the point. They don’t care about you, they don’t care about the game. They care about self gratification. They will be part of a GM city and attack whatever and whoever they want. That’s on the small scale.<P>Then you will have the Uber guilds. These will be guilds devoted to money and power. They will conquer for no reason. They will kill for no reason. They will take your items and give them to newbies who just joined their guild. This will bring more members of course. Organized crime.<P>These kids ( for the most part they are younger people) will get together and gank you for no reason. Report them to your guild? Put them on your most hated list? who cares! they sure as hell wont. They will kill you and be killed. But they will always come out on top unless you sink to their level.<P><BR>Its not EQ thinking. Its common sense. I’ve been playing online games for many years. SB looks like it will be a good game, it looks like it will bring a new flavor to the market. But please, don’t tell me its gonna change everything. When your talking about no rules player killing (Former Ultima Online) your gonna have many problems unless its well thought out. <P><BR>Im sure you have played Ultima Online. I would play the game on my days off. Start in the morning. You know when the game got bad? 3:00pm. You know why? This is when the kids got home from school. You would be mining the side of a mountain minding your own business. 6 PKs come running through and kill you for no reason, take your stuff and laugh at you. All of this and more will happen in SB. <P>Open your eyes my friend. This game is different. But it’s the same people playing it.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P><BR>P.S  You better hope there is a big niche market as you put it. Or SB wont last 6 months.
