<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I just recently started playing UO again, and I got PKed when I wandered outside of Britain(Couple of the warrior magi paralyzed me and double-teamed me.  Pretty cowardly), but I was back on my feet in less than fifteen minutes.  Just had to buy more armor, new weapon and shield, and a new horse.  So, I don't think it'll be a terrible blow(Except maybe to one's ego) when you're PKed in SB.  Items are important, but with soul-binding and the fact that most normal equipment can be purchased in a city, it won't be any problem to me.  I hate item dependency, so the only thing I'll probably want that's of any use will be a good sword.<P>And, as far as me PKing for loot, I will only loot a corpse if some non-roleplaying PK or PKs try to attack me and fail.  I'll be roleplaying an Elf-hater, so if I go around killing Elves for roleplaying reasons I will NOT loot their corpses.  That would be unsportsmanlike.  I'll also not kill Elves that are so many levels below me that they'd have no chance of winning(If I'm level 70 and a level 10 Elf chances by, for example).<P>So, while I think there will be lots of PKs in the game(Grief, roleplaying, what-have-you), I don't think it will be as bad as some people are thinking.  I think it will be fairly easy to bounce back and fairly easy to exact your revenge.   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
