<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Morello - Well said.  I couldn't agree more.  I've also been said to be every one of those people and more depending on whos talking.  Not to mention someone's hero, a nice guy, etc, as well.  My personal favorite was hacker though, when I wasn't hacking.   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>Pro EQ: The EQ mindset thing was directed at the predictions, not you.  Just to clear things up.  <P>Anyway most of the people I usually play these games with don't pay very much attention to message boards.  Over the last few months I've had to define terms such as griefer, etc.  They just didn't know what this meant or what kind of player these guys were.  Even thought they all played Meridian, UO, EQ, etc.  <P>Why?  Simple.  Because I can name the people that fit into these categories on <B>one</B> hand that have ever bothered us in all of these games combined.<P>You just have to learn how to play with them.  "Play smarter" as Morello put it.  Most griefers I know never make it anywhere substantial.  So how long do you really have to deal with them?  They become more sparse the higher up you go (levels).  While they continue to grief play and are killed everywhere they go you continue to level.  Eventually you have almost no grief players to even worry about.  <P>More often than not if you ignore them they go away anyway.  I know "innocent" people whine.  I killed a TON of "darkies" on Vallon Zek Teams PvP server.  More often than not, save the larger guilds for some reason, when I killed them I had to listen to them complain.  I never gloated, never told them they suck, sometimes I never even looted.  But man did I hear about the evil I had just done.  Could it be that people bring these types of players upon themselves?  Heres a tip, when someone kills you congratulate them ooc or just shutup write their name down and either get back later or watch out for them.  Anything else will simply earn you grief.<P>Anyway Pro I expect these things to happen.  In all honesty when this happens to you it might be my friends and I doing it if you  happen to be an elf.  For your loot?  To ruin your day?  No, to fight real people.  Competition if you will.  More entertaining than any AI.  It just doesn't bother me, even when it happens to me.  What to you is a problem to me is just part of the game.
</FONT>
